div id="emailPreHeader" style="mso-hide:all; visibility:hidden; opacity:0; color:transparent; mso-line-height-rule:exactly; line-height:0; font-size:0px; overflow:hidden; border-width:0; display:none !important;">Hear how to succeed in today’s freight market.
 
 
 
Join our next one-hour, live webinar to hear the latest trends impacting your truckload, LTL, ocean, and air freight. You’ll get answers to your shipping questions and our experts will offer tools to help you win in today’s market. Find out what’s important right now, including:
  • How supply and demand trends look for 2022
  • When the congestion at the ports will end
  • Which LTL strategies to employ for success in this market
  • How to prepare for areas of ongoing market tension
  • What pricing and labor changes could impact your freight
Get answers to your most pressing issues—submit your questions when registering or ask during the live event. We’ll help you gain a deeper understanding of the market with information you can use to gain a competitive advantage.

The OOCL Montreal voyage 572 is now scheduled to arrive at Section 62 (Racine), where import (Inbound) cargo will be discharged. 

Current ETA is Sunday February 6, 2022

Please ensure that custom release documentation is modified accordingly


Export (outbound) cargo continues to be accepted at Section 77 (Cast Terminal)
